directly ratio esitimation

target_data$population = NULL
target_data_dropPop = target_data
target_data = NULL
source_data$population = NULL
source_data_dropPop = source_data
source_data = NULL
target_data_dropPop[is.na(target_data_dropPop)] <- 0
source_data_dropPop[is.na(source_data_dropPop)] <- 0

densratio_obj_uLSIF <- densratio(source_data_dropPop,target_data_dropPop)
## ################## Start RuLSIF ##################
## Searching optimal sigma and lambda...
##   sigma = 0.001, lambda = 0.001, score = 0.000
##   sigma = 0.010, lambda = 0.001, score = -0.000
##   sigma = 0.032, lambda = 0.001, score = -0.000
##   sigma = 0.100, lambda = 0.001, score = -0.160
##   sigma = 0.316, lambda = 0.032, score = -2.271
## Found optimal sigma = 0.316, lambda = 0.032.
## Optimizing kernel weights...
## End.
## ################## Finished RuLSIF ###############
density_ratio = densratio_obj_uLSIF$compute_density_ratio(source_data_dropPop)
summary(density_ratio)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max.

check the spatial dsitribution is correct

loa_shape <- readOGR("/home/z/zhendong/london/enriched_feature/loa_enriched.shp")
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
## Source: "/home/z/zhendong/london/enriched_feature/loa_enriched.shp", layer: "loa_enriched"
## with 4835 features
## It has 50 fields
## Integer64 fields read as strings:  USUALRES HHOLDRES COMESTRES HHOLDS TWEETS_DIS DISTINCT_T
loa_shape@data["D_pred_xg"] = as.integer(descaled_loa_transferred_predict)
loa_shape@data["T_pop_xg"] = loa_or_data$population
loa_shape@data["residual"] = loa_shape@data$D_pred_xg - loa_shape@data$T_pop_xg
loa_shape@data["residual_abs"] = abs(loa_shape@data$residual)
writeOGR(loa_shape,dsn ="/home/z/zhendong/london/enriched_feature/XGboost",layer = "4_moa2loa_xgboost_spatial_uLSIF",driver = "ESRI Shapefile")
